[src:warp-rust-web/rust-programming-language] Statements in Rust are separated by semicolons.
[src:warp-rust-web/rust-programming-language] Variables in Rust are defined through the `let` keyword.
[src:warp-rust-web/rust-programming-language] The example below assigns a value to the variable with name `foo` of type `i32` and outputs its value; the type annotation `: i32` can be omitted.
